INSTALL
=======

1. Install rsync
   ==> pacman -S rsync (@Arch Linux)
2. Build inotify
   ==> make inotify 
3. Build open_dropbox
   ==> make all

USAGE
=======

1. Create some folder you want use as syncronization folder
   ==> mkdir /home/<Your username>/OpenDropbox

2. Edit the configfile, if it not exist just create one
   ==> create: touch odb.conf
   ==> edit  : syncFolder = /home/<Your username>/OpenDropbox/
       	       destFolder = /<syncronization>/<Folder>/

3. Start the programm
   ==> ./odb --config=odb.conf

4. Enjoy the your syncronization deamon without doing anything

TRICKS
=======

* You don't need to copy data into you syncronization folder.
  The easiest way is just creating symlinks into it.
  ==> cd /home/<Your username>/OpenDropbox
  ==> ln -s ../<New Folder> .


